THEN the "streams" call has {{pubads.g.doubleclick.net*}} as the request URL
AND the "publica" call has {{pbs.getpublica.com*}} as the request URL
AND {{PUBLICA}} is listed under {{adCapabilities}} in the {{graphql}} call for {{initPlaybackSession}}

THEN DataDog should display log event.action as {{player_state_change}} and a event.reason as {{media_recovery}}
AND {{media_recovery}} has a {{metadata.details}} field that looks like so: {{media recovery attempted due to buffering error. Number of attempts: buffering - 1, fatal - 0}} 

*Per Nolan this metadata.details will persist in all future events until updated, including but not necessarily limited to {{bitrate_dropped}}, {{buffering_recovered}}, {{buffering_started}}, and {{playback_ended events}}

